comment_text: Now that's what I call a real revolution of the Walker Universe! ‚ù§‚ù§‚ù§üé∂üé∂üñ§ Time is also my favorite song by Hans Zimmer.ü§£üòä.But I should also probably thank you, Alan, for giving the fact that you're the reason I made the best EDM Project in 8th grade last year. Your songs inspired me quite a lot over the years but faded and heading home-like, I was like no he didn't just create a real-life World OF Walker and traveled all over the world to make it's revolution true. Like seeing all the different places you and your team traveled to, just tell everyone that's how much you love your career as a DJ and a musician. And I couldn't be happier from all the work you've been doing, up until now. And not just for your self, but also the distance you've gone to make all your fans happy, and even if you'd had your downs. Still, the fact that I and many other people and walkers and other musicians can look up to you and say "I wanna be Alan Walker when I grow up'' that really just amazes me, because, before any of this, you were just like every other typical DJ, making music in their room. And if it weren't for those people out there to search like crazy for your work, you would've still been in that room creating music. Therefore I'm actually happy you posted your songs online, even if you thought some of them weren't fully perfect.CAuse really no matter how many songs you've done in the past and now, all your walker fans love it. Because you are not just giving them a right to be who they want to be, but to also make them stand up and be that someone. And I just still can't believe how far you've made it, it's crazy insane but also amazing. Like I've seen many DJ'S before, but you started from search to creating your own evolution and your own story, and well I just wanted you to know that after all this LONG text, at the end of the day...I'll always be your number one fan, and no matter what happens, how much hate goes on from non-walkers.I'll always love and support you, because what you've done to support us and make us feel like a walker family isn't big enough to say thank you. You know I was in love with Avicii's music too, and when I heard he died. That hit me hard, cause I really looked up to him in so many ways, and I lost hope for a while and fell into a major sadness and storm of thoughts. And when I came across your music, your live videos here and on Instagram, some of my hope was restored and the fact that many DJ'S made a tribute to him, that healed me even more. Your music helped me get back up and look at a life a totally different way, and I'm just really thankful your still around and you still will be when this coronavirus finally vanishes once in for all, wish you the best of luck and I can't wait to hear more from you.\n~Indira Lechiguero\nAnd to all those people who read through the comments, pls don't be mean to me or Alan, cause I'm not trying to get his attention at all, I just wanna take a moment to appreciate all his work and thank him for inspiring me as any other fan would. Writing a lot is just a thing I tend to do.
